Process called "extract_current_call_stack_names" returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract actual function names from current call stack with symbol resolution
            Let stack_trace be Traceback.capture_current_stack_trace
    Let function_names be list containing For each frame in stack_trace:
    If "function_name" in frame:
            Add to function_names frame["function_name"]
    Otherwise if "symbol_name" in frame:
            Add to function_names frame["symbol_name"]
    Otherwise:
            Let address_hex be Traceback.convert_integer_to_hex_string with number as frame["instruction_pointer"]
    Add to function_names ("function_at_" concatenated with address_hex) Note: If no stack trace available, analyze execution context
    If length of function_names = 0:
            Let execution_context be Traceback.get_current_execution_context
    If "current_function" in execution_context:
            Add to function_names execution_context["current_function"]
    Otherwise:
            Add to function_names "<executing_function>"
            Return function_names

Process called "get_current_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Get actual current thread ID from runtime thread management
    Let thread_info be Traceback.get_runtime_thread_info If "current_thread_id" in thread_info:
    Return thread_info["current_thread_id"] Note: Calculate thread ID from thread-specific information
            Let thread_id be Traceback.calculate_thread_id_from_stack_pointer
            Return thread_id

Process called "collect_execution_context" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Collect comprehensive execution context from current runtime state
    Let execution_context be dictionary containing Note: Collect local variables from current scope
            Let current_frame be Traceback.get_current_execution_frame
            Let local_variables be extract_local_variables_from_frame with frame as current_frame
    Set execution_context["local_vars"] to local_variables Note: Collect function parameters
            Let function_parameters be extract_function_parameters_from_frame with frame as current_frame
    Set execution_context["parameters"] to function_parameters Note: Collect call stack context
            Let call_stack_depth be Traceback.calculate_current_call_stack_depth
    Set execution_context["call_depth"] to call_stack_depth Note: Collect thread context
            Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Set execution_context["thread_id"] to thread_id Note: Collect timing context
            Let current_timestamp be TimeCore.get_system_time_nanoseconds
    Set execution_context["timestamp_ns"] to current_timestamp Note: Collect memory context
            Let memory_usage be get_current_memory_usage_bytes
            Set execution_context["memory_usage_bytes"] to memory_usage Return execution_context

Process called "collect_performance_metrics" returns PerformanceMetrics:
    Note: Collect real-time performance metrics from hardware and system
    Let performance_metrics be dictionary containing Note: Get CPU performance data
            Let cpu_counters be HardwareTimer.read_performance_counters
