Process called "get_current_parent_call" that takes session as TemporalDebugSession returns FunctionCall:
    Note: Get current parent function call from call tree with stack analysis
    Let call_tree be session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree If call_tree = null or length of call_tree.active_calls = 0:
    Return null Note: Find current active call stack depth
    Let current_depth be calculate_current_call_depth with session as session If current_depth < or equal to 1:
    Return null Note: No parent for root call Note: Get parent call from active call stack
            Let parent_depth be current_depth - 1
    Let active_calls be call_tree.active_calls For each call in active_calls:
    If call.call_depth = parent_depth:
    Return call Note: Fallback: search by call stack correlation
            Let current_stack be extract_current_call_stack_names
    If length of current_stack > 1:
    Let parent_function_name be current_stack[1] Note: Parent is one level up For each call in active_calls:
    If call.function_name = parent_function_name:
            Return call Return null

Process called "calculate_current_call_depth" that takes session as TemporalDebugSession returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate actual current call depth from stack analysis and call tree
            Let call_stack be extract_current_call_stack_names
    Let stack_depth be length of call_stack Note: Verify depth with call tree if available
            Let call_tree be session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree
    If call_tree is not equal to null and length of call_tree.active_calls > 0:
    Note: Find deepest active call depth
            Let max_tree_depth be 0
    For each call in call_tree.active_calls:
    If call.call_depth > max_tree_depth:
    Set max_tree_depth to call.call_depth Note: Use the more accurate depth measurement
    If max_tree_depth > 0 and max_tree_depth is not equal to stack_depth:
    Note: Call tree depth is more accurate for active debugging
    Return max_tree_depth 1 Note: Current call is one deeper Note: Cross-verify with execution context
            Let execution_context be collect_execution_context
    If "call_depth" in execution_context:
            Let context_depth be execution_context["call_depth"]
    If context_depth > 0 and context_depth is not equal to stack_depth:
    Note: Take the maximum of all depth measurements for accuracy
            Return if context_depth > stack_depth then context_depth else stack_depth Return stack_depth

Process called "add_function_call_to_tree" that takes session as TemporalDebugSession and call as FunctionCall returns Boolean:
    Note: Add function call to execution call tree with proper hierarchical structure
    Let call_tree be session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree Note: Initialize call tree if empty
    If call_tree = null:
            Set session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree to create_empty_function_call_tree
    Set call_tree to session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree Note: Add to active calls list
    Add to call_tree.active_calls call Note: Establish parent-child relationships
    If call.call_depth > 1:
            Let parent_call be get_current_parent_call with session as session
    If parent_call is not equal to null:
            Set call.parent_call_id to parent_call.call_id
    If parent_call.child_calls = null:
            Set parent_call.child_calls to list containing
    Add to parent_call.child_calls call.call_id Note: Update call tree statistics
            Set call_tree.total_calls to call_tree.total_calls 1
    If call.call_depth > call_tree.max_depth:
    Set call_tree.max_depth to call.call_depth Note: Index call by ID for fast lookup
            Set call_tree.calls_by_id[call.call_id] to call Return true

Process called "find_function_call_by_id" that takes session as TemporalDebugSession and id as String returns FunctionCall:
    Note: Find function call by ID in call tree with fast lookup
    Let call_tree be session.execution_timeline.function_call_tree If call_tree = null:
    Return null Note: Fast lookup using indexed calls
    If id in call_tree.calls_by_id:
    Return call_tree.calls_by_id[id] Note: Fallback: linear search through active calls
    For each call in call_tree.active_calls:
    If call.call_id = id:
    Return call Note: Search through all recorded calls if not in active list
    If "all_calls" in call_tree:
    For each call in call_tree.all_calls:
    If call.call_id = id:
            Return call Return null

Process called "calculate_total_child_time" that takes call as FunctionCall returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total execution time of all child function calls
    If call.child_calls = null or length of call.child_calls = 0:
    Return 0 Let total_child_time be 0 Note: Sum execution time of all direct children
    For each child_call_id in call.child_calls:
    Note: Look up child call (would need session context for full implementation)
    Note: For now, calculate based on timing data structure
    If "child_timing_data" in call.metadata:
            Let child_timings be call.metadata["child_timing_data"]
    If child_call_id in child_timings:
            Let child_duration be child_timings[child_call_id]
    Set total_child_time to total_child_time child_duration Note: Alternative calculation from nested calls in timing data
    If total_child_time = 0 and "nested_calls" in call.timing_data:
            Let nested_calls be call.timing_data["nested_calls"]
    For each nested_call in nested_calls:
    If "duration_ns" in nested_call:
            Set total_child_time to total_child_time nested_call["duration_ns"] Return total_child_time

Process called "update_function_performance_metrics" that takes call as FunctionCall returns Boolean:
    Note: Update comprehensive performance metrics for function call
    Let current_metrics be call.performance_metrics Note: Update timing statistics
    If "duration_ns" in call.timing_data:
            Set current_metrics["total_duration_ns"] to call.timing_data["duration_ns"]
    Set current_metrics["self_time_ns"] to call.self_time_ns Note: Calculate efficiency ratio
    If call.self_time_ns > 0:
            Let efficiency_ratio be call.self_time_ns / call.timing_data["duration_ns"]
    Set current_metrics["efficiency_ratio"] to efficiency_ratio Note: Update CPU performance metrics
    If "cpu_cycles" in current_metrics:
            Let cycles_per_ns be current_metrics["cpu_cycles"] / current_metrics["total_duration_ns"]
    Set current_metrics["cycles_per_nanosecond"] to cycles_per_ns Note: Update memory performance metrics
    If "memory_bytes" in current_metrics:
            Let memory_mb be current_metrics["memory_bytes"] / 1048576
    Set current_metrics["memory_mb"] to memory_mb If current_metrics["total_duration_ns"] > 0:
            Let memory_rate be current_metrics["memory_bytes"] / (current_metrics["total_duration_ns"] / 1000000000)
    Set current_metrics["memory_bytes_per_second"] to memory_rate Note: Update call frequency statistics
    If "call_count" in current_metrics:
            Set current_metrics["call_count"] to current_metrics["call_count"] 1
    Otherwise:
    Set current_metrics["call_count"] to 1 Note: Calculate performance grade
            Let performance_grade be calculate_function_performance_grade with metrics as current_metrics
            Set current_metrics["performance_grade"] to performance_grade Set call.performance_metrics to current_metrics
            Return true

Process called "is_temporal_hotspot" that takes call as FunctionCall returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if function call is a temporal performance hotspot
    Let performance_metrics be call.performance_metrics Note: Check execution time threshold
    If "total_duration_ns" in performance_metrics:
    Let duration_ns be performance_metrics["total_duration_ns"] Note: Consider hotspot if execution time > 10ms
    If duration_ns > 10000000:
    Return true Note: Check CPU cycles threshold
    If "cpu_cycles" in performance_metrics:
    Let cpu_cycles be performance_metrics["cpu_cycles"] Note: Consider hotspot if CPU cycles > 1M cycles
    If cpu_cycles > 1000000:
    Return true Note: Check memory usage threshold
    If "memory_bytes" in performance_metrics:
    Let memory_bytes be performance_metrics["memory_bytes"] Note: Consider hotspot if memory usage > 10MB
    If memory_bytes > 10485760:
    Return true Note: Check call frequency threshold
    If "call_count" in performance_metrics:
    Let call_count be performance_metrics["call_count"] Note: Consider hotspot if called frequently (> 1000 times)
    If call_count > 1000:
    Return true Note: Check efficiency ratio
    If "efficiency_ratio" in performance_metrics:
    Let efficiency_ratio be performance_metrics["efficiency_ratio"] Note: Consider hotspot if efficiency is low (< 30%)
    If efficiency_ratio < 0.3:
            Return true Return false

Process called "analyze_hotspot_temporal_patterns" that takes session as TemporalDebugSession and call as FunctionCall returns Boolean:
    Note: Analyze temporal patterns in hotspot function for optimization insights
    Let analysis_results be dictionary containing Note: Analyze call frequency patterns over time
            Let frequency_pattern be analyze_call_frequency_pattern with session as session and call as call
    Set analysis_results["frequency_pattern"] to frequency_pattern Note: Analyze execution time variance patterns
            Let timing_variance be analyze_execution_timing_variance with call as call
    Set analysis_results["timing_variance"] to timing_variance Note: Analyze memory allocation patterns
            Let memory_pattern be analyze_memory_allocation_pattern with call as call
    Set analysis_results["memory_pattern"] to memory_pattern Note: Analyze CPU utilization patterns
            Let cpu_pattern be analyze_cpu_utilization_pattern with call as call
    Set analysis_results["cpu_pattern"] to cpu_pattern Note: Identify temporal correlations with other functions
            Let correlation_analysis be analyze_temporal_correlations with session as session and call as call
    Set analysis_results["correlations"] to correlation_analysis Note: Generate optimization recommendations
            Let optimization_recommendations be generate_hotspot_optimization_recommendations with analysis as analysis_results
    Set analysis_results["recommendations"] to optimization_recommendations Note: Store analysis results in call metadata
    Set call.metadata["hotspot_analysis"] to analysis_results Note: Log hotspot analysis for monitoring
            Let log_success be log_hotspot_analysis_results with call as call and analysis as analysis_results Return log_success

